&lt;h2&gt;About the role&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an Engineering Manager for Cloud Platform Engineering, you will lead a team responsible for the infrastructure, deployment platforms, CI/CD standards, Kubernetes environments, Terraform modules, observability practices, and operational foundations that enable Exiger engineering teams to build and run reliable software at scale.&lt;br&gt;This role is ideal for an engineering leader with recent experience managing platform, infrastructure, DevOps, SRE, or cloud engineering teams. You do not need to be the deepest hands-on expert in every tool, but you should be able to guide technical direction, evaluate tradeoffs, challenge designs, coach engineers, and partner with leadership on platform strategy.&lt;br&gt;The role will work closely with frontend, backend, infrastructure, security, and product teams, but the primary focus is cloud platform engineering, operational excellence, infrastructure standards, and scalable delivery practices.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/h2&gt;
