&lt;li&gt;Set technical direction for Exiger’s cloud platform, including AWS infrastructure, Kubernetes-based application delivery, Terraform/IaC standards, CI/CD, observability, and operational practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define short-term and long-term platform priorities and ensure active projects align with engineering and business goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with application engineering teams to provide reusable platform capabilities, self-service workflows, documentation, and operational standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as an organizational resource to unblock and enable multiple engineering teams across diverse platform and infrastructure challenges.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead major platform initiatives that improve reliability, scalability, security, developer productivity, and cost efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Instill and promote a culture of learning, engineering excellence, ownership, and platform accountability across engineering.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own standards for runbooks, platform documentation, incident response readiness, and operational knowledge sharing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Guide CI/CD, deployment, rollback, testing, and self-healing architecture improvements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with AWS account teams and internal stakeholders to evaluate AWS services and influence adoption where appropriate.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to planning, staffing, and financial decisions that support the long-term success of the platform team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead hiring, technical interview calibration, and team growth planning for platform engineering

