&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who We Are:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Exiger transforms supply chains into a strategic advantage, advancing our mission to make the world a safer and more transparent place to succeed. Our&lt;span data-ogsb=&quot;rgb(255, 255, 255)&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;AI platform, 1Exiger&lt;/span&gt;, delivers instant visibility into complex supplier ecosystems, leveraging proprietary data and advanced AI to surface risk, automate compliance, and unlock&lt;span class=&quot;Apple-converted-space&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ogsb=&quot;rgb(255, 255, 255)&quot;&gt;efficiencies and cost savings to strengthen long-term resilience&lt;/span&gt;. Trusted by 550+ global customers, including Fortune 500 companies and U.S. government agencies, Exiger is a recognized, award-winning leader in supply chain AI and a FedRAMP® authorized provider to the federal government.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lead Forward Deployed Engineer – Defense Supply Chain Risk Programs&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; Huntsville, Alabama (Hybrid Position)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Department:&lt;/strong&gt; Federal Programs&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Type:&lt;/strong&gt; Full-Time&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Program Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Exiger is seeking a Lead Forward Deployed Engineer to expert guidance, direction, and organize the delivery of solutions and scale delivery of advanced analytics and AI-enabled capabilities supporting Army sustainment and supply chain risk management programs. This role drives the end-to-end execution of data-driven solutions—including AI/LLMs, data pipelines, and risk models—that enhance visibility, resilience, and readiness across the defense industrial base.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Lead Forward Deployed Engineer will operate at the intersection of program leadership, data engineering, and sustainment operations. The successful candidate will collaborate closely with engineers, data scientists, and Army stakeholders to translate mission requirements into scalable, technically sound analytics workflows that directly inform risk mitigation and acquisition decisions across Army portfolios.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead and manage a team of engineers developing for analytics and AI-driven solutions supporting Army sustainment, acquisition, and supply chain risk management missions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Direct the development and deployment of databases, data pipelines, risk models, mitigation strategies, and analytic workflows to identify and mitigate systemic supply chain vulnerabilities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive program execution by defining technical methodologies, prioritizing development milestones, and managing delivery of mission-ready analytical capabilities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate complex sustainment and acquisition requirements into actionable tasks for engineering and data science teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee QA/QC for data and model outputs, ensuring results are technically valid, reproducible, and operationally relevant to Army decision-makers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide technical oversight of analytics integration into sustainment workflows, ensuring compliance with Army policy and information assurance standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with cross-functional teams—including engineers, product research analysts, and industrial base experts—to deliver measurable mission impact.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Facilitate coordination between technical teams, program leadership, and Army stakeholders, ensuring program transparency, accountability, and timely reporting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications – Required&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10+ years of experience in front-end, back-end, or full-stack software development

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who We Are:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Exiger transforms supply chains into a strategic advantage, advancing our mission to make the world a safer and more transparent place to succeed. Our&lt;span data-ogsb=&quot;rgb(255, 255, 255)&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;AI platform, 1Exiger&lt;/span&gt;, delivers instant visibility into complex supplier ecosystems, leveraging proprietary data and advanced AI to surface risk, automate compliance, and unlock&lt;span class=&quot;Apple-converted-space&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ogsb=&quot;rgb(255, 255, 255)&quot;&gt;efficiencies and cost savings to strengthen long-term resilience&lt;/span&gt;. Trusted by 550+ global customers, including Fortune 500 companies and U.S. government agencies, Exiger is a recognized, award-winning leader in supply chain AI and a FedRAMP® authorized provider to the federal government.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Learning and Development Specialist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Location: McLean&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Work Environment: Hybrid&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Summary:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a unique opportunity to join a fast-growing SaaS company at a pivotal stage of scale, where revenue enablement is viewed as a strategic lever for growth, not a support function. Exiger is investing in how it goes to market, in how it frames value, supports complex buying decisions, and equips revenue teams to perform consistently in long, multi-stakeholder sales cycles. The Head of Revenue Enablement will play a central role in shaping this next phase, working across Sales, Product, Marketing, Revenue Operations, and Learning &amp;amp; Development. If you thrive in ambiguous environments, enjoy building from first principles, and want to directly influence how a global revenue organization performs, this role offers both scope and impact.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Exiger is seeking a proactive, highly motivated, self-driven Learning &amp;amp; Development (“L&amp;amp;D”) Specialist who thrives in fast-paced, high-demand environments and is ready to build, scale, run, and continuously improve the Learning and Development program.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role will work with partners in Product, Global Shared Services and Go-To-Market (“GTM”). Reporting to the Head of Learning &amp;amp; Development the role will work with their L&amp;amp;D peers to equip customer-facing staff and other internal stakeholders with the knowledge and tools needed to drive adoption of Exiger’s tech solutions. They will also design scalable learning content, help to iterate L&amp;amp;D operations, integrate AI into learning workflows, proactively identify gaps before they become problems, and utilize AI tools to vastly increase productivity. The ideal candidate is hungry to learn, unafraid to ask questions, highly resourceful, and comfortable operating with autonomy in a rapidly&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and deliver new hire onboarding, GTM certifications, and training programs for customer-facing teams to reduce ramp time and increase tech solution fluency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and deliver training, enablement, and ongoing optimization of core sales tools (e.g., Salesforce, Clari, Consensus, 6Sense, etc.).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, develop, and continuously refine training bots that simulate realistic customer conversations and product scenarios for enterprise sellers and client-facing teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Using AI tools design role-based micro-trainings that can be quickly deployed and easily updated as tech solutions and messaging evolve.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be proactive in identifying opportunities to automate, accelerate, or enhance learning experiences using AI and improve onboarding processes, documentation standards, and training workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
